# Project Standards

Architecture, Go, and domain standards to keep consistency and quality.

## Architecture (Clean Architecture)
Expected structure and dependencies between layers. See examples in [README.md](mdc:README.md).

## Domain (DDD)
- Core entities: Principal, Role, Permission, MembersRequest, DefaultRoles
- Business rules in entities and use cases

## Go Standards
- Imports formatted with goimports
- Intention-revealing names
- Errors with context (e.g., `fmt.Errorf("...: %w", err)`)
- Use `context.Context`
- Package-level declarations (variables, constants, types, functions) can be referenced across files within the same package